[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Reviewing Java test coverage**\n\nI’m puzzled over the rule that requires active class coverage in its own dedicated Java test file. Adding a fixture class might violate the one-to-one rule? It states that all top-level test classes should be public, but what about a fixture that isn’t a test? I’m also considering the implications of dynamically accessing classes like `com.ibm.security.krb5.KrbException` and whether the test can instantiate it directly. I wonder if reflection metadata is necessary for dynamic class loading in a native image?\n\n**Considering Class.forName in native images**\n\nI’m thinking about whether `Class.forName` can resolve constants in a native image, and it seems likely. I need to make sure the test doesn’t use a `$` name, which is good! I can set `java.vendor` to IBM and then call `fromException` with a new `com.ibm.security.krb5.KrbException(7)`. When the static initialization loads the com.ibm class, it should invoke the `returnCode` method on the cause and return `SERVER_NOT_FOUND`. Sounds manageable!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_05392daa5b634e640169f2bfb83554819eb2614944b8df7eb0\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8r_EGRe06c3GbNWSxFRHZitqvgUVnxdchXAO08s7PDRXWfFKZPCQP-CAB0gc0CF_VDDugk3u8xlzE_Gedk3SfU987YT-hvzY7bD98lJ3bQPlb8LcTLIEmP_YguYJ2ssEE7NxhRF_HQ98KY9IPecfYZ3vOKj6lRrF2F8XxZrlLKWUjRmYNJtumVZuV943vk1ylnr7az-0g870lQT4-n37GXVQDMSkuBlwFrC8H2j-C9C0g2LhmJlCtmjojdFZFtAeuffcz-ATiQFleDh6vszFigQoQCi6iL_anAd36Ux1rKlD90Boh1_xoZTJyCb9TybRv17xdYSLNYagJ4tt7uax8dCVJ_MG-7nuF4-G08c8mrvU_Td0BXcKMUaiV8srDcA3zVfY67wBlWpuuehoOJ8PeZIpKSUU-Ks1KG2zHYpqx1RTb13W7r2MQAPXeTk47mZrm8temq5wSbSKGCVh9wVzsyuueDoYlqiqZLFclY5otA9fAOWN82FFtwSlFmM3dnBRgGxTmmhID9wrID9KY0OAxFgiJF75NBZtKawsmaCsLU-Q6rnuZ4-QeQKkJYa3t7_wSycDz-zu1I1vpHkrS7iktawz7WR9AdOGPsu_7WM9E-2c0Qybo_aDcwv7SFT7xrBI8voVPqRY25j21aWC-NCHDl3oSuyd6pHZBaghuzKSIntBS3bgLyry9Yb_GxZ