YcOKVY2uRgUk-ZUVo_WnJwU-XTkskIKlzx723QQepr4qms1Ebq3XnoinfmkRi9-X2B80=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reviewing Java test coverage**\\n\\nI’m puzzled over the rule that requires active class coverage in its own dedicated Java test file. Adding a fixture class might violate the one-to-one rule? It states that all top-level test classes should be public, but what about a fixture that isn’t a test? I’m also considering the implications of dynamically accessing classes like `com.ibm.security.krb5.KrbException` and whether the test can instantiate it directly. I wonder if reflection metadata is necessary for dynamic class loading in a native image?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Class.forName in native images**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether `Class.forName` can resolve constants in a native image, and it seems likely. I need to make sure the test doesn’t use a `$` name, which is good! I can set `java.vendor` to IBM and then call `fromException` with a new `com.ibm.security.krb5.KrbException(7)`. When the static initialization loads the com.ibm class, it should invoke the `returnCode` method on the cause and return `SERVER_NOT_FOUND`. Sounds manageable!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_t8ZsYW14rp5U7gjOAVgW3byc|fc_05392daa5b634e640169f2bfc453cc819eb703e59c5fabc7a6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/KerberosErrorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_kafka.kafka_clients;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertFalse;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\n\nimport org.apache.kafka.common.security.kerberos.KerberosError;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class KerberosErrorTest {\n    @Test\n    void resolvesKerberosErrorFromIbmKrbExceptionCause() {\n        String originalVendor = System.getProperty(\"java.vendor\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.vendor\", \"IBM Corporation\");\n        try {\n            Exception exception = new Exception(new com.ibm.security.krb5.KrbException(7));\n\n            KerberosError error = KerberosError.fromException(exception);\n\n            assertSame(KerberosError.SERVER_NOT_FOUND, error);\n            assertFalse(error.retriable());\n        } finally {\n            restoreProperty(\"java.vendor\", originalVendor);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreProperty(String key, String value) {\n        if (value == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(key);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(key, value);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 292, "output": 1254, "cacheRead": 26112, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27658, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777516471052, "responseId": "resp_05392daa5b634e640169f2bfb78154819e8a1bf4e392d8d322"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_t8ZsYW14rp5U7gjOAVgW3byc|fc_05392daa5b634e640169f2bfc453cc819eb703e59c5fabc7a6", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1296 bytes to tests/src/org.apache.kafka/kafka-clients/4.2.0/src/test/java/org_apache_kafka/kafka_clients/KerberosErrorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777516485662}]}
